Return the mean and the HPDI of the parameters of the model

Source: R/bpc_get_parameters.R
get_parameters.Rd

Return a data frame with the mean and with high and low 95% hpd interval or credible interval for all parameters of the model

get_parameters(
  bpc_object,
  params = NULL,
  HPDI = TRUE,
  n_eff = TRUE,
  Rhat = FALSE
)

Arguments

bpc_object

a bpc object
params

a vector with the parameters to use. If null then all will be present
HPDI

should return the HPDI or the credible intervals. Default is returning the HPDI
n_eff

Should include the number of effective samples in the df
Rhat

Should include the Rhat in the df

Value

a data frame containing a column with the parameters, a column with mean and two columns with higher and lower intervals

Examples

# \donttest{
m<-bpc(data = tennis_agresti,
player0 = 'player0',
player1 = 'player1',
result_column = 'y',
model_type = 'bt',
solve_ties = 'none')
